%% Diagram: Snapshot + stream switchover (DBLog watermark technique)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Source DB
    participant Log as Transaction Log
    participant CDC as CDC Connector
    participant WM as Watermark Table
    participant Sink as Downstream Sink

    Note over CDC,Sink: Streaming is already running.\nA chunk of historical rows is needed.

    CDC->>Log: Pause emitting chunk-conflicting log events
    CDC->>WM: UPDATE watermark SET id = uuid_low (LOW)
    Log-->>CDC: Replays LOW marker
    CDC->>App: SELECT chunk WHERE pk BETWEEN :a AND :b
    App-->>CDC: Chunk rows (in-memory buffer)
    CDC->>WM: UPDATE watermark SET id = uuid_high (HIGH)
    Log-->>CDC: Replays HIGH marker

    Note over CDC: Reconcile - drop chunk rows whose key\nwas modified between LOW and HIGH.\nThose events arrive on the live stream.

    CDC->>Sink: Emit surviving chunk rows (snapshot events)
    CDC->>Sink: Continue forwarding live log events
    Note over CDC: Repeat per chunk.\nSnapshot is resumable, no table locks.
